OL,6,FAt least 72 people under the age of 18
OL,7,Fare believed to have been charged.
OL,9,FA number of people have also been
OL,10,Fhanded charges relating to publishing
OL,11,Fmaterial that contributed to rioting,
OL,12,Fsuch as publishing written material to
OL,13,Fstir up racial hatred or sending a
OL,14,Fgrossly offensive message.
OL,16,FMs Cooper said: "For too long
OL,17,Fgovernments have failed to address the
OL,18,Frise in extremism, both online and on
OL,19,Four streets, and we've seen the number
OL,20,Fof young people radicalised online
OL,21,Fgrow.
